Date: 0/0/1898
Source: Austral English
Author: MORRIS
Vol / Page: 345
Edition:
Quote: <i>Peg out, v</i>. to mark out a gold-claim under the Mining Act, or a <i>Free-Selection</i> (q.v.) under the Land Act, by placing pegs at the corners of the land selected. Used also metaphorically. [1858]
